  "riddle": "1. Unearth the tale of a global powerhouse born in 1964, initially known for its running shoes. What is the establishment year of this sneaker titan?\n\n2. What iconic sneaker made its debut in the 1980s and became synonymous with a basketball legend? Find its launch date.\n\n3. This football club, often called \"The Red Devils,\" has a storied history. How many subsections about its past can you count within the chapter on History?\n\n4. Dive into the world of sports media, where one network rules — what stake does a leading entertainment conglomerate hold in this broadcasting giant, expressed as a percentage?\n\n5. Flip those digits around. What new number emerges from the ownership figure you just uncovered?\n\n6. Venture to the region famously known for its evergreen forests. Within the population section, how many leading cities are noted in the list of urban centers?\n\n7. On a different note, check the market for the automotive company starting with \"F.\" What was the closing stock price for this entity on November 16, 1984?\n\n8. In the realm of automobiles, a certain Detroit-based manufacturer holds a pivotal place in history. What year did this automotive legend come into existence?\n\n9. The beloved animation studio that brought us timeless characters also has roots. Identify the year that marked its founding.\n\n10. If you were to calculate the number of days between November 17, 1984, and March 17, 2026, how many would you find?\n\n11. This number now holds a secret in its binary form. How many 1-bits can be counted in that digital representation? \n\n12. In the sunny city noted for its Rose Bowl, what is the altitude at which it proudly sits above sea level?\n\n13. When seeking the elevation of that same city, what concrete figure do you discover resting in the geographical records?\n\n14. Explore the hospitality landscape. How many places to rest can one find in close proximity to this charming city renowned for its festivals?\n\n15. Com